'''Radiation intelligence''', or '''RINT''', is [[military intelligence]] gathered and produced from unintentional radiation created as [[Electromagnetic induction|induction]] from electrical wiring, usually of computers, data connections and electricity networks.<ref>{{cite book |title=Intelligence and the National Security Strategist |last=George |first=Roger Z. |author2=Robert D. Kline |author3=Mark M. Lowenthal |year=2006 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-0-7425-4039-2 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jJxyIb2hN4MC&pg=PA173&dq=%22Radiation+intelligence%22+%2BRINT&num=100&client=firefox-a&sig=ACfU3U2_Unk7iSPj0FXZjq3T8V87lw_oBg |accessdate=2008-09-19 |page=173}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=How It Works |last=Horobin |first=Wendy |year=2002 |publisher=Marshall Cavendish |isbn=978-0-7614-7330-5 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=TyMEEI6-LH4C&pg=PA2255&dq=%22Radiation+intelligence%22+%2BRINT&num=100&client=firefox-a&sig=ACfU3U3A791UmgJxUdlxvTKqy9MUJrDvXA |accessdate=2008-09-19 |page=2255}}</ref>
