[[File:Saint Charles Reservoir (Colorado).JPG|275px|thumb|right|Saint Charles Reservoir No. 3, viewed from the Stem Beach overpass.]]
'''Saint Charles Reservoir''' is the name of three reservoirs in [[Pueblo County, Colorado]]. The first one, called just '''Saint Charles Reservoir''', is located in the mountains of southwestern [[Pueblo County, Colorado|Pueblo County]], southwest of [[Beulah, Colorado|Beulah]], at an elevation of {{convert|8894|ft|m|abbr=off|sp=us}}. It is located at {{Coord|38|00|00|N|105|02|35|W|display=inline}}.<ref>{{cite gnis |id= 199075 |name= Saint Charles Reservoir}}</ref>

'''Saint Charles Reservoir Number 2''' and '''Saint Charles Reservoir Number 3''' are located next to each other in [[Stem Beach, Colorado|Stem Beach]], just south of [[Pueblo, Colorado|Pueblo]].<ref>{{cite gnis |id= 193779 |name= Saint Charles Reservoir Number 2}}</ref><ref>{{cite gnis |id= 193778 |name= Saint Charles Reservoir Number 3}}</ref> Reservoirs number 2 and 3 were built by [[Colorado Fuel and Iron]] in the early 1900s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.greenhornvalleyview.com/index.asp?linkID=63&itemID=8138 |title=Stem Beach |last=Huban |first=Cheryl Johnson |date=2013-03-06 |website=Ghv.com |publisher= |access-date=2018-02-18 |quote=}}</ref> All three reservoirs are privately held and not open to the public.

