[[File:Vejo jegaine, 2006-09-02.jpg|thumb|Wind turbine in Lithuania]] '''Wind power in Lithuania''' is a form of [[renewable energy in Lithuania]]. At the end of 2011 wind power capacity in [[Lithuania]] was 179 MW and the [[wind energy]] share of total electricity consumption was 3,8%.<ref name="EU2011">{{cite web|title= Wind in power - 2011 European statistics |url= http://www.ewea.org/fileadmin/ewea_documents/documents/publications/statistics/Stats_2011.pdf |publisher= ewea.org | format = pdf |date=February 2012|accessdate=2012-06-06 }}</ref> At the end of 2018 wind power capacity in [[Lithuania]] was 521 MW and the [[wind energy]] share of total electricity consumption was 12%.<ref>[https://www.vz.lt/energetika/2018/05/03/pirmaji-ketvirti-vejo-jegaines-lietuvoje-pagamino-per-30-elektros-energijos]</ref>
